<h4 id="Article-122199">SpaMedica visits Liverpool's Whitechapel Centre to help the homeless</h4>
<div id="imageContent321ac53c796c45228a2269e8fbef3f2b">
</div>
<p>Three SpaMedica staff  members visited the Whitechapel Centre in Liverpool last week in a drive to help the city's homeless in the run up to winter.</p>
<p>Our staff took scarves, socks, hats and gloves donated by SpaMedica, and distributed them to the homeless people who dropped by.</p>
<p>A local optometrist was also present, giving free eye tests to the many people who turned up. This was an invaluable service, helping people who cannot easily access healthcare services. A free hot lunch was also served. </p>
<p>Our staff found the day very rewarding, and SpaMedica is delighted to support such a good cause. Photos of the event can be seen <a href="https://www.facebook.com/SpaMedica-589567857851193/?ref=hl">here</a>.</p>
<p> </p>
<p class="last-updated">Last updated on 25 November 2015.</p>
